#- Dear Reader,§0
§0
§0Thanks for reading the inaugural issue of the Mt. Augusta Buyer's Guide. My vision is a weekly issue with new prices, since prices update so quickly in game, but we'll see where this goes. I'm releasing this first issue at cost to produce, 
#- but I plan on introducing advertisements in later issues. I will keep these advertisemetns non-intrusive and separate from the actual prices. I will also be experimenting with converting prices into either and iron or diamond standard and hope to be able 
#- to use the Civ Mecantile Exchange for that. On that note, the CME is not included in this buyer's guide due to the nature of the exchange being very volatile. I hope to find a way to include its prices into this buyer's guide. I hope that everyone found 
#- this guide useful. Any suggestions or price corrections can be sent to me at /user/Higgenbottoms on reddit or Higgenbottoms#2186 on discord. §0
§0
§0Buy Local,§0
§0Higgenbottoms§0
§0Editor
#- 